A coroner in Ohio has found that the 
father of a boy killed in a 2012 school shooting died of an accidental 
heroin overdose on the second anniversary of his son's death.

The
 Geauga County coroner confirmed Friday that 48-year-old Russell King 
Sr. succumbed to the combined effects of heroin and alcohol.

A family 
member found King dead at his home in Aquilla Village just after 5am on the morning of February 27.

